<div class="html_content"><p><span style="font-family:'Roboto Slab','Arial';font-weight:700;font-size:1.857em;color:rgba(53,181,235,1);">HOW WE WORK</span></p><p style="margin:1.43em 0em 0.36em 0em;line-height:1.69014084507042;"><span style="font-family:'Roboto','Arial';font-weight:300;font-size:1.143em;color:rgba(34,34,34,1);">We admit one cohort of 60 participants grouped into 4 parallel sessions. This will give us an opportunity to shape up the trainers, obtain all the resources, assess the demand and expectations and do necessary reviews. As we assess, we can strategize on how to scale. The various models of scaling could include offering evening classes, increasing the number of students per class, offering similar modes in the other five colleges or even running. During the two months, surveys will be done to explore what works best in light of students’ availability, semester load, distance students cover to attend the face to face classes, delivery methods, class sizes, University management appreciation, among others. This will then inform how best to scale </span></p><p style="margin:1.43em 0em 0.36em 0em;line-height:1.69014084507042;"><span></span></p></div>
